199 gold medals, 199 silver medals and 275 bronze medals are at stake in the Khelo India School Games. The country’s brightest talent in the under-17 age group will compete in the Games.
The games will highlight India’s young sporting talent and showcase India's sports potential.
The Khelo India School Games are being held from 31st January to 8th February, 2018 in New Delhi. Under-17 athletes have been invited to participate across 16 disciplines.
Talented players identified in priority sports disciplines at various levels by a High-Powered Committee will be provided annual financial assistance of Rs. 5 lakh per annum for 8 years.
आर्थिक सर्वेक्षण 2017-2018 : राजकोषीय घाटे में लगातार गिरावट।pic.twitter.com/vuBjB4s0rH
In keeping with Prime Minister's vision, Khelo India is expected to help find young talent from the schools in various disciplines and groom them as future sports champions.

The Khelo India programme has been introduced to revive the sports culture in India at the grass-root level by building a strong framework for all sports played in our country and establishing India as a great sporting nation.
Prime Minister @narendramodi will launch the first Khelo India School Games at Indira Gandhi Indoor Stadium in New Delhi tomorrow.

Democracy in India is the bedrock of our nation. We take pride in telling the world we are the largest democracy even if we aren’t the oldest or the greatest.
It is certainly not a BJP v/s Congress or a Rahul v/s Modi issue. It is quite simply an issue that should concern every single Indian.
“Democracy in India is in danger”. This was the warning that came from the Hon Judges yesterday. So no, it’s not an internal matter for the Hon SC.

Government under the leadership of PM @narendramodi ji has taken several initiatives to boost quality & productivity of jute, ease procurement and enhance income of jute farmers through targeted interventions. Here is a glimpse of various initiatives undertaken:pic.twitter.com/6Tey70PmY2

Underlining the importance of diversification of jute industry, emphasis will be given to diversification by incentivising use of jute geo-textiles and promoting jute as eco-friendly fibre both in domestic and global markets.

Jute mill workers will not be deprived of their statutory dues as a special mechanism will be setup in consultation with State Governments to link Production Control and Supply Order to ensure timely payment.
Cabinet Decision on Mandatory Packaging in Jute Material also allows provision for 100% packaging of food grains in jute bags provided industry is able to meet the requirement.

Government purchases over Rs. 5500 crore jute products to cater to core demand of the sector. Therefore today’s decision will further help in sustaining demand for jute and support livelihood of Jute workers.

Grateful thanks to PM @narendramodi ji & Union Cabinet for approving extension norms for Mandatory Packaging in Jute Material. This decision mandating 90% of food grains and 20% sugar products to be packed in jute bags will benefit nearly 3.7 lakh workers & 40 lakh farmers.pic.twitter.com/rkpbYLoR7W
